<article>
    <h1>The Best Give Ever this fes&#xAD;tive sea&#xAD;son</h1>
    <h2>Turn your gifts into &#x201C;gives&#x201D; and help over 580 lo&#xAD;cal char&#xAD;i&#xAD;ties weather the im&#xAD;pact of Covid-19 by do&#xAD;nat&#xAD;ing, vol&#xAD;un&#xAD;teer&#xAD;ing or fundrais&#xAD;ing via Giv&#xAD;ing.sg</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201209/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-09"><time>2020-12-09</time></a>
        - <span>SINGAPORE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Giv­ing.sg is your sim­ple, se­cure and trusted na­tional giv­ing plat­form that con­nects the pub­lic with over 580 reg­is­tered char­i­ties in Sin­ga­pore.</p>
    <p>In this pan­demic-bat­tered econ­omy, Giv­ing.sg has be­come one of the most ac­ces­si­ble plat­forms for non-profit or­gan­i­sa­tions to gar­ner sup­port, as vol­un­teer and do­na­tion num­bers have dropped by 80 per cent since the cir­cuit breaker.</p>
    <p>“Char­i­ties were hit hard dur­ing the pan­demic as they had to can­cel their phys­i­cal fundrais­ers. Hence, they have to fo­cus on vir­tual fundrais­ing on Giv­ing.sg. We con­nect over 390,000 users with the char­i­ties, and fre­quently com­mu­ni­cate to the pub­lic on the giv­ing op­por­tu­ni­ties and the im­pact they can make,” says Mr Jef­frey Tan, Direc­tor of Mar­ket­ing & Ad­vo­cacy, Na­tional Vol­un­teer and Phi­lan­thropy Cen­tre.</p>
    <p>Through Giv­ing.sg, char­i­ties like YMCA of Sin­ga­pore raised $340,000, funds that were es­sen­tial in help­ing them sus­tain their Covid-19 ini­tia­tives where they dis­trib­uted meals to vul­ner­a­ble groups dur­ing the cir­cuit breaker pe­riod.</p>
    <p>Here’s how you, too, can make an im­pact via Giv­ing.sg and build a City of Good!</p>
    <p>Giv­ing is sim­ple and se­cure</p>
    <p>You can make di­rect mone­tary do­na­tions to reg­is­tered char­i­ties un­der the Com­mis­sioner of Char­i­ties, such as the Cere­bral Palsy Al­liance Sin­ga­pore, or sup­port in­di­vid­u­als and or­gan­i­sa­tions in their fundrais­ing ef­forts through Giv­ing.sg.</p>
    <p>Just click the “Do­nate To­day” tab, and choose from the cat­e­gories of char­i­ties, cam­paigns and causes avail­able. Browse a com­pre­hen­sive list of char­i­ties and causes rang­ing from those sup­port­ing the el­derly to that of an­i­mal wel­fare.</p>
    <p>You could also view detailed de­scrip­tions of how your do­na­tion will make a dif­fer­ence, and choose to make a one-time or monthly con­tri­bu­tion. Do­nat­ing on­line at Giv­ing.sg is a se­cure process, as the web­site uses a safe pay­ment gate­way and an en­crypted server.</p>
    <p>Vol­un­teer­ing is eas­ier than ever</p>
    <p>If you’ve got time and tal­ent, why not give by vol­un­teer­ing? Aside from phys­i­cal ac­tiv­i­ties such as be­friend­ing the el­derly at se­nior cen­tres, there are also vir­tual and off­site vol­un­teer­ing op­tions avail­able.</p>
    <p>You can help man­age a cri­sis in­ter­ven­tion hot­line with the Sa­mar­i­tans of Sin­ga­pore, take se­niors on a vir­tual tr­ishaw ride with Cy­cling with­out Age Sin­ga­pore to beat so­cial iso­la­tion or be­come a vir­tual em­cee for CCF Fam­ily Day, an on­line event by the Chil­dren’s Can­cer Foun­da­tion hap­pen­ing on Dec 19.</p>
    <p>With so many op­por­tu­ni­ties to choose from, the pos­si­bil­i­ties are end­less.</p>
    <p>And if your strength lies in ral­ly­ing peo­ple to sup­port your cause, try kick­start­ing an in­di­vid­ual fundrais­ing project for a char­ity on Giv­ing.sg. Just sign up for an ac­count via the web­site, se­lect a non-profit to raise funds for, write an inspiring cam­paign story on why you chose to help, and share it on your so­cial me­dia pages and with your net­work of fam­ily and friends!</p>
    <p>You can se­lect up to four causes that will ben­e­fit from this cam­paign, and de­ter­mine the fundrais­ing du­ra­tion. It’s that sim­ple!</p>
    <p>We are very en­cour­aged to see mem­bers of the pub­lic ris­ing to the oc­ca­sion and join­ing us to set up their own fundrais­ing pages. We are very glad to be a part of this move­ment.</p>
    <p>Mr Steve Loh, Gen­eral Sec­re­tary & CEO, YMCA of Sin­ga­pore</p>

